This memorandum, issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr., outlines the policy of the Administration to combat and respond to the COVID-19 pandemic. The memorandum directs the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to provide a 100 percent Federal cost share for all work eligible for assistance under Public Assistance Category B. This includes work related to emergency protective measures in response to COVID-19, performed from January 20, 2020, through July 1, 2022. The memorandum also includes general provisions that clarify its implementation and limitations.